name: 16 Quick-and-Easy Side Dish Recipes for the Air Fryer
Best Holiday Party Appetizers to Make in the Air Fryer
Air Fryer Lemon Garlic Parmesan Chicken
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'skinless boneless chicken thighs'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon zest'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Place chicken in a large bowl. Add garlic, lemon zest, paprika, oregano, salt, and crushed red pepper; toss to coat chicken in the seasonings.. Combine Parmesan cheese and panko in a shallow dish. Dredge chicken in Parmesan mixture to coat. Sprinkle any remaining mixture over chicken; pat to adhere.. Coat the chicken generously with cooking spray.. Lightly coat air fryer basket with cooking spray. Place chicken in prepared basket (cook in batches, if needed). Air fry 12 minutes or until an instant-read thermometer inserted in the center reads 170 degrees F (77 degrees C).. Serve immediately.

name: Our 15 Best Air Fryer Thanksgiving Recipes
Air Fryer S’Mores
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'sleeve', 'name': 'graham crackers'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': '(1.5 ounce)', 'name': 'chocolate candy bars'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': None, 'name': 's’more-sized marshmallows'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 380 degrees F (193 degrees C). Lay out a total of 10 graham crackers. Do not break apart.. Take 10 s’more size marshmallows and cut them in half horizontally with a serrated knife. Place the sticky side of each marshmallow half onto each square side of a graham cracker rectangle.. Place a piece of parchment into the air fryer basket; place a graham cracker into the basket, marshmallow side facing up. Air fry until marshmallow is toasted, 3 to 4 minutes. Remove carefully.. Gently break marshmallow-topped graham cracker rectangle into 2 squares, add a chocolate bar half on top of 1 square, and sandwich the chocolate with the other square.

name: Air Fryer Baked Yams
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'yam'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Scrub yam clean and dry with a paper towel. Rub all over with olive oil.. Place yam in the preheated air fryer, and cook until tender when pierced with a fork, 15 to 20 minutes.

name: Lemon Garlic Butter Chicken Spiedini
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white wine, such as Pinot Grigio'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon zest'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'skinless boneless chicken thighs'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'Italian breadcrumbs'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'skewers'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fresh parsley'}
steps: Whisk together olive oil, wine, 2 tablespoons lemon juice, lemon zest, 1/2 of the garlic, crushed red pepper, oregano, 1 teaspoon salt, and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in a bowl. Add chicken and toss to coat. Cover and refrigerate 30 minutes to 1 hour.. Stir together remaining salt and pepper with bread crumbs, panko, Parmesan cheese, and garlic powder in a shallow dish. Remove chicken from marinade and toss to coat in breadcrumb mixture, pressing to adhere as necessary. Thread chicken onto skewers and coat with olive oil cooking spray.. Preheat an air fryer to 390 degrees F (198 degrees C).  Air fry until chicken is no longer pink at the center and juices run clear, and is until lightly golden brown and crisp, about 12 minutes. An instant read thermometer, inserted near the center, should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Meanwhile, melt butter with remaining garlic in a microwave-safe dish on High in the microwave, about 10 seconds.  Stir in remaining lemon juice and parsley. Drizzle butter mixture over chicken just before serving.

name: Air Fryer Grilled Pimento Cheese
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'French bread,'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pimento cheese spread'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'tomato'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried basil'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt and freshly ground black pepper'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 370 degrees F (188 degrees C).. Spread one side of each bread slice lightly with mayonnaise. Lay 2 slices of bread, mayonnaise side down, and evenly spread with pimento cheese; top with tomato slices. Sprinkle with basil and season with salt and pepper. Top with remaining 2 bread slices, mayonnaise side up.. Move sandwiches to the air fryer basket. Place a toothpick in the center of each sandwich and air fry until bread is fully toasted and golden brown, 8 to 10 minutes, flipping halfway through.. Remove toothpick from sandwich, slice in half, and serve.

name: Air Fryer Chicken Parmesan
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': '2 (8-ounce)', 'name': 'boneless skinless chicken breasts, patted dry'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt, divided'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper, divided'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, lightly beaten'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'seasoned panko (Japanese-style breadcrumbs)'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'armesan cheese, plus more for garnish'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'crushed red pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'marinara sauce, plus more for serving'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mozzarella cheese'}
steps: Gather all ingredients.. On a cutting board, butterfly chicken by cutting each breast in half widthwise to create 4 thin pieces of chicken; season both sides with 1/2teaspoon of the salt and 1/4 teaspoon of the black pepper.. Place flour, egg, and panko in 3 separate shallow dishes. Add Parmesan, oil, crushed red pepper, and garlic powder to panko; stir to coat. Add remaining 1/4 teaspoon salt and remaining 1/4 teaspoon black pepper to flour; stir to combine. Working with 1 chicken piece at a time, dredge chicken in flour; shake off excess. Dip in egg; let excess drip off. Dredge in panko mixture to coat; place on a plate.. Preheat a 6-quart air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) for 2 minutes. Working in two batches, add 2 chicken cutlets to the air fryer basket in a single layer. Cook until chicken is golden brown on both sides, about 5 minutes per side.. Top each chicken piece with 1/4 cup marinara and 1/4 cup mozzarella cheese.. Snugly fit all 4 breasts in a single layer in air fryer basket; cook at 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) until cheese is melted and browned and a thermometer inserted into the thickest portion of chicken registers 165 degrees F (73 degrees C), 2 to 3 minutes.

name: Air Fryer Eggplant
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'eggplant'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'avocado oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried thyme'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Place a disposable paper liner in the air fry basket or give it a spritz of cooking spray.. Stir eggplant cubes in a large bowl with avocado oil. Sprinkle with garlic powder, thyme, lemon pepper, and salt. Toss until all pieces are well coated.. Place the eggplant cubes in a single layer in the air fryer basket, and mist with cooking spray. Cook until browned on the outside and tender inside, 15 to 17 minutes, shaking the basket halfway through. Serve immediately.

name: Air Fryer Sriracha Fries
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 to 3', 'unit': None, 'name': 'russet potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'riracha'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}
steps: Cut potatoes into fries. Place cut fries into a bowl of water; soak for 1 hour.. Preheat the oven to 200 degrees F (95 degrees C). Line a baking sheet with paper towels and set a wire rack over the sheet.. Preheat the air fryer to 375 degrees F according to manufacturer’s instructions.. Drain fries, and pat dry with a paper towel. Place fries in a resealable plastic bag. Add oil, 1 tablespoon Sriracha, and salt. Seal the bag and toss to coat.. Add fries to bottom of air fryer basket in a single flat layer, not stacked. You will have to work in batches.. Air fry until crispy and golden brown, about 13 minutes.. Place fries on the prepared baking sheet; keep warm in the preheated oven. Repeat with remaining fries.. Place fries on a platter; drizzle with remaining sriracha. Enjoy.

name: Crispy Air Fryer Potato Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'red potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer’s instructions.. Place cubed potatoes in a large bowl. Add olive oil and toss to coat. Add garlic powder, salt and pepper; toss again. Add grated Parmesan and toss one last time.. Place seasoned potatoes in the basket of the preheated air fryer. Cook for 8 minutes. Shake and cook until tender, about 4 minutes more. Serve immediately.

name: Copycat Wingstop Cajun Corn
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ears', 'name': 'corn'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'thyme'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}
steps: Cut corn into 2-inch thick pieces. Toss corn with olive oil, 1 teaspoon salt and 2 tablespoons melted butter.. Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions. Add corn to air fryer and cook about 15 minutes, tossing occasionally, until partially golden brown.. Meanwhile, combine remaining salt and butter with remaining ingredients in a large bowl and mix well.. Add cooked corn to butter mixture  and toss well to coat.

name: Air Fryer Po' Boy
ingredients: {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chopped fresh tarragon'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'Dijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(14 ounce) package', 'name': 'shredded coleslaw mix'}, {'quantity': '¾', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'buttermilk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'hot pepper sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground dried chipotle pepper'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1 ½', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'large shrimp - peeled, deveined, and tails removed'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'whole wheat panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': '(6 inch)', 'name': 'whole-wheat hoagie rolls, split and toasted'}
steps: To make the coleslaw: Whisk lemon juice, oil, garlic, tarragon, mustard, and 1/4 teaspoon kosher salt together in a bowl. Add coleslaw mix and toss to coat. Set aside.. Whisk buttermilk, hot sauce, cayenne, chipotle pepper, black pepper, and remaining salt together in another bowl. Add shrimp to buttermilk mixture, tossing to coat; let marinate for a few minutes.. Meanwhile, preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions.. Add 2/3 cup panko to a shallow dish. Remove shrimp from buttermilk mixture, letting excess drip off. Working in 3 batches, dredge 1/3 of the shrimp in 2/3 cup panko, turning evenly to coat. Transfer to a baking sheet and repeat with remaining shrimp and panko.. Working in batches if necessary, arrange shrimp in a single layer in the fryer basket. Cook, turning once, until shrimp are golden brown and cooked through, about 8 minutes.. To serve, put coleslaw in rolls and top with shrimp.

name: Air Fryer Buffalo Wings
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'sea salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'mustard powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground coriander'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'chicken wings'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 380 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Combine sea salt, garlic powder, mustard powder, coriander, smoked paprika, cayenne pepper, and black pepper in a shallow bowl. Dredge each chicken wing in the spice mixture and set into the air fryer basket in one layer.. Cook in the air fryer until chicken wings are no longer pink at the bone and the juices run clear, about 30 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). If wings are smaller, reduce cooking time.

name: Air Fryer Smashed Potatoes
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'baby gold potatoes'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'melted unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'freshly ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'chopped fresh parsley for garnish (Optional)'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Meanwhile, place potatoes in a microwave-safe bowl: cook on high until just tender, about 5 minutes.. Transfer potatoes to a baking sheet and use the bottom of a small glass to gently "smash" them to 3/4 or 1/2-inch thick. The thinner you flatten the potatoes, the crispier they will be.. Brush melted butter over the tops of smashed potatoes. Season with salt, garlic powder, and pepper.. Place potatoes in the basket of the air fryer in an even layer; cook until golden and crisp, about 10 minutes. Garnish with parsley and serve hot.

name: Air Fryer Quesadillas
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': None, 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded cheese'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'nonstick cooking spray'}
steps: Heat tortillas in the microwave until pliable, about 15 seconds.. Place 1/4 cup cheese on one half of each tortilla; fold other half of tortilla over cheese. Place in  air fryer. Spray with non-stick cooking spray.. Set temperature to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Place quesadillas in the basket of the air fryer, and cook until golden brown, 4 to 6 minutes. Flip quesadillas, press down with a spatula, and air fry an additional 2 to 3 minutes.

name: Air Fryer Truffle Polenta Fries
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(18 ounce) tube', 'name': 'polenta'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'black truffle-infused olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'truffle zest seasoning'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'shredded Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'fresh parsley'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer's instructions. Line a baking sheet with paper towels; set aside.. Cut the tube of polenta in half widthwise. Cut each half in half lengthwise and then cut into 1/2-inch wide fry-shaped sticks.. Whisk truffle-infused olive oil and truffle zest in a bowl. Add fries and gently toss to coat.. Place fries in the basket of the air fryer in a single layer. Depending on the size of your air fryer, fries may need to be cooked in batches.. Cook for 10 minutes. Shake the basket and cook 5 minutes more. Using tongs, transfer fries to the prepared baking sheet. Garnish with Parmesan and chopped parsley.

name: Air Fryer Firecracker Salmon Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'balsamic vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'brown sugar'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil,'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'minced garlic'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ginger'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'crushed red pepper flakes, or more to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'kosher salt'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'salmon filets'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Combine balsamic vinegar, brown sugar, oil, soy sauce, garlic, ginger, red pepper, and salt in a bowl and whisk well. Set aside half of marinade for serving.. Add salmon to remaining marinade in the bowl and toss lightly to coat. Cover with plastic wrap and marinate in the refrigerator for at least 30 minutes, and up to 4 hours.. Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) for 2 to 3 minutes, or according to manufacturer’s instructions. Spray air fryer basket with nonstick cooking spray.. Add salmon in a single layer, cooking in batches if necessary, and cook until salmon flakes easily with a fork and is lightly browned and crisp around the edges, 6 to 8 minutes. Serve drizzled with reserved sauce.

name: Air Fryer Chicken Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pound', 'name': 'boneless chicken breasts,'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon juice, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'talian seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper (optional)'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C) setting  for 5 minutes.. Stir melted butter, olive oil, lemon juice, garlic, Italian seasoning, salt, paprika, and cayenne together in a large bowl. Add chicken pieces, and toss to coat thoroughly. Place chicken pieces in a single layer in the air fryer basket. You may have to cook them in batches.. Air fry in the preheated fryer until chicken is no longer pink at the center and juices run clear, 8 to 10 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the center should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).

name: 4 Ingredient Air Fryer Pepper Poppers
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'bell pepper, any color'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1 (1', 'unit': 'ounce)', 'name': 'ranch dip mix'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'bacon bits'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 390 degrees F (199 degrees C) according to manufacturer’s instructions.. Quarter the bell pepper lengthwise. Remove stem, membrane, and seeds; discard. Cut each quarter in half lengthwise.. Mix cream cheese, ranch dip mix, and bacon bits together in a bowl until evenly combined. Using a spoon, divide mixture between pepper slices, about 1 1/2 to 2 teaspoons per slice.. Place stuffed bell peppers in the basket of the air fryer. Cook until cheese filling is lightly browned, 8 to 10 minutes. Check after 8 minutes as air fryers vary.

name: Air Fryer Bell Pepper Poppers
ingredients: {'quantity': '9', 'unit': 'mini pepper', 'name': 'mini bell peppers'}, {'quantity': '5.2', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'Gournay cheese'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon, each cut into 3 short pieces'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh parsley for garnish (optional)'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C), according to manufacturer’s directions.. Slice each mini-pepper in half, from stem to tip. Remove membranes and seeds. Fill each mini-pepper with Boursin and place a piece of bacon on top.. Place filled mini-pepper halves in a single layer in the air fryer and cook until bacon is as crisp as you like, 8 to 12 minutes. Air fry in batches, if necessary.. Place on a serving platter, garnish with parsley, and serve warm.

name: Air Fryer Cinnamon Roll Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 (12.4', 'unit': 'ounce)', 'name': 'cinnamon rolls'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'white sugar'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground cinnamon'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "confectioner's sugar"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'orange peel'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'orange juice'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'icing'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 325 degrees F (165 degrees C) according to manufacturer’s instructions. Add sugar and cinnamon to a large resealable plastic bag, and shake to combine.. Remove the 8 cinnamon rolls from the can, and set icing aside. Cut each roll into 4 equal pieces for a total of 32 bites.. Line the fryer basket with parchment paper. Place the bites in a single layer in the bottom of the basket, cook for 3 minutes, turn over using tongs, and cook until golden brown, another 2 to 3 minutes. Depending on the brand and size of your air fryer, you may have to cook in batches, and your timing may vary, so watch closely.. Meanwhile, prepare the dip. Add cream cheese, confectioner’s sugar, orange zest, orange juice, and the packaged icing to a small bowl. Beat with an electric mixer on medium speed until you reach a dipping consistency, about 1 minute.. Drop the warm pieces into the sugar-cinnamon mixture, and shake. Transfer to a plate or basket, and serve with the dip.

name: Air Fryer Ham and Cheese Wraps
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': '(7-inch', 'name': 'flour tortillas'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'spicy mustard'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'thin slices', 'name': 'deli ham'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'olby-Jack cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}
steps: Place tortillas on a clean work surface. Spread 1 tablespoon mustard in a thin, even layer over each tortilla, leaving a 1/2-inch edge free of mustard.. Place 2 slices of ham on each tortilla. Top each tortilla with 1 slice of cheese. Fold opposing edges of the tortilla to overlap the filling. Roll 1 of the opposing edges around the filling creating a burrito.. Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C) according to manufacturer’s instructions.. Brush tops of wraps with melted butter. Place wraps in the basket of the air fryer. Cook for 6 minutes.. Using tongs, transfer wraps to a cutting board. Cut in half and serve immediately.

name: Air Fryer Buffalo Cauliflower
ingredients: {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': "Buffalo wing sauce (such as Frank's)"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(2 pound)', 'name': 'cauliflower, broken into florets'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '½', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': "seasoned salt (such as Lawry's)"}, {'quantity': '¼', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'drizzle of buffalo wing sauce (optional)'}
steps: Combine hot sauce, butter, and honey in a large bowl; whisk until well combined. Add cauliflower florets and stir until well coated.. Combine flour, cornstarch, garlic powder, seasoning salt, and paprika in a separate bowl, stirring well. Gradually sprinkle the flour mixture over the cauliflower florets, tossing until all florets are coated.. Preheat the air fryer to 390 degrees F (195 degrees C). Spray the fryer basket with olive oil spray or line with a parchment liner.. Transfer cauliflower florets to the air fryer basket in a single layer, making sure not to overcrowd the basket, so they'll crisp up and not turn soggy.. Air fry for 10 to 15 minutes, shaking the basket several times until the florets are lightly browned. They should be crispy, but not overcooked or mushy. You may have to cook in batches depending on the size of your air fryer. Time may vary depending on the size and brand of your air fryer.. Give the cauliflower a light drizzle of buffalo wing sauce when they come out of the air fryer, if desired. Serve with your choice of a creamy dipping sauce.

name: Air Fryer Honey-Mustard Chicken Thighs
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': None, 'name': 'boneless skinless chicken thighs'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'smoked paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ijon mustard'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'olive oil cooking spray'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 390 degrees F (198 degrees C), if recommended by the manufacturer. Pat chicken thighs dry with paper towels.. For sauce, combine onion powder, garlic powder, smoked paprika, salt, and pepper in a small bowl. Stir in  honey and Dijon mustard.. Spray one side of chicken thighs with olive oil spray, and place oiled side down in the air fryer in a single layer. Brush the tops of the chicken thighs with the sauce.. Air fry at 390 degrees F (198 degrees C) for 8 minutes.. Carefully turn chicken thighs, and brush with remaining sauce. Continue air frying until internal temperature of chicken reaches 165 degrees F (74 degrees C), when tested with an instant-read thermometer, 6 to 8 minutes more. Serve warm.

name: Air Fryer Hearts of Palm Sticks
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'talian bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1 (14', 'unit': 'ounce) can', 'name': 'hearts of palm, drained'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Stir flour, salt, and pepper together in a shallow bowl. Beat egg with a fork in a separate shallow bowl. Stir together Italian breadcrumbs, Panko breadcrumbs, and grated Parmesan in a third shallow bowl.. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Roll 1 heart of palm in seasoned flour, dip it in egg, then roll in seasoned bread crumbs. Place on the prepared baking sheet. Repeat with remaining hearts of palm.. Transfer the baking sheet to a freezer for 20 minutes.. Meanwhile, preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Spray hearts of palm sticks with olive oil and place in the basket of the preheated air fryer. Cook for 6 minutes. Roll sticks over and cook until coating is crisp, about 6 minutes more. Serve immediately.

name: Air Fryer Cheesy Bacon Ranch French Fries
ingredients: {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'frozen French fries'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ranch salad dressing mix'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'bacon bits'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded Cheddar cheese'}
steps: Preheat an air fryer to 400 degrees Fahrenheit (200 degrees C). Place frozen French fries in a large bowl.. Whisk olive oil and dry ranch salad mix in a separate small bowl until smooth. Pour olive oil mixture over the fries and toss to coat. Add bacon bits and salt. Toss again.. Place seasoned fries in the basket of the air fryer. Cook for 7 minutes. Shake the basket and cook 5 minutes more.. Sprinkle shredded cheese over the fries. Cook 2 minutes. Using a spatula, transfer to a serving platter and serve immediately.

name: Air Fryer Mini Dark Chocolate Cake with Brown Butter Frosting
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flour, plus more for dusting cake pan'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsweetened Dutch process cocoa powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'baking soda'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'buttermilk'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsweetened applesauce'}, {'quantity': '4 1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': ''}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'dark chocolate, chopped, plus more for garnish'}, {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'powdered sugar'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'water, or as needed'}
steps: Preheat air fryer to 320 degrees F (160 degrees C). Coat a 6-inch cake pan with cooking spray. Line bottom of pan with parchment paper; dust with 2 tablespoons flour, tapping out excess.. Stir together 1/4 cup flour, the cocoa, baking powder, baking soda, and salt in a small bowl. In another small bowl, whisk together buttermilk, applesauce, oil, espresso powder, and vanilla.. In a third bowl, beat egg with an electric mixer at low speed. Gradually add sugar. Increase mixer speed to high and continue beating until mixture is thick and pale, about 2 minutes.. Alternately fold flour mixture and buttermilk mixture into egg mixture with a rubber spatula, stirring until incorporated before adding next addition. Fold in dark chocolate.. Pour batter into the prepared pan. Arrange pan in the air fryer basket.. Cook until a toothpick inserted in center comes out clean, about 25 minutes. Let cool in pan on a wire rack about 10 minutes. Remove cake from pan and allow to cool completely on a wire rack.. For the frosting, melt butter in a heavy saucepan over medium heat; cook, stirring occasionally, until butter begins to turn golden brown and smells nutty, 15 to 20 minutes. Transfer butter to a bowl; cool for 10 minutes.. Whisk in honey and vanilla. Whisk in powdered sugar until smooth, adding water, 1 teaspoon at a time, until desired consistency. The frosting will look separated but will come together with whisking in water a little at a time.. Immediately top cooled cake with the frosting and garnish with additional dark chocolate.

name: Air Fryer Spanakopita
ingredients: {'quantity': '2 (10-', 'unit': 'ounces) pkg.', 'name': 'spinach, thawed and squeezed dry'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'feta cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'shredded mozzarella cheese'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'grated Parmesan cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'clove garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'lb. pkg.)', 'name': 'phyllo dough, thawed'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'unsalted butter, melted'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'tzatziki sauce for serving'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh dill for serving'}
steps: For filling, stir together spinach, feta, mozzarella, Parmesan, and garlic in a bowl. Line a baking sheet with parchment paper.. Arrange 1 sheet of phyllo on a clean work surface and brush lightly with some of the melted butter. Top with 2 more phyllo sheets and more butter. Cover remaining phyllo with a damp towel while you work. Cut phyllo stack lengthwise into 3 (3-inch-wide) strips.. Spoon about 1 tablespoon filling at the bottom of each strip. Take the bottom right corner and fold the dough over the filling to make a triangle. Fold the bottom left corner up to make another triangle. Continue folding until all the dough is folded. Arrange spanakopita, seam side down, on the prepared baking sheet. Lightly brush with butter. Repeat with remaining phyllo, filling, and butter.. Preheat air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Arrange spanakopita in an even layer in the air fryer basket, working in batches as needed.. Cook, turning once halfway through, until spanakopita is golden brown, 12 to 15 minutes. Cool slightly. Serve with tzatziki sauce and dill.

name: Air Fryer Pecan Crusted Trout
ingredients: {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'chopped pecans'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried rosemary, crushed'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '4 (4-', 'unit': 'ounces) rainbow', 'name': 'trout fillets, thawed if frozen, skinned if desired'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'maple syrup'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon wedges, for serving'}
steps: Preheat air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Stir together pecans, rosemary, and salt in a shallow dish. In a second shallow dish, add flour. In a third shallow dish, lightly beat egg. Dip one side of each fillet in flour, shaking off excess; dip into egg, then into pecan mixture, lightly pressing to coat fish.. Working in batches if needed, arrange fillets on parchment paper, pecan-coating up. Transfer fish on parchment to the air fryer basket.. Cook until fish easily flakes with a fork and an instant-read thermometer inserted into thickest part of fillets registers 145 degrees F (62 degrees C), 7 to 8 minutes.. Drizzle fillets with maple syrup and serve with lemon wedges.

name: Air Fryer Blooming Onion
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika, plus more for garnish'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried thyme'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cumin'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large (14- to 16-ounces)', 'name': 'sweet onion'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cream-style horseradish sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried oregano'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'black pepper'}
steps: Preheat air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Whisk together milk and egg in a bowl until combined. In a large bowl, stir together flour, salt, cayenne pepper, paprika, black pepper, oregano, thyme, and cumin.. Slice 1 inch off the top of the onion and remove papery skin. Remove a 1-inch-diameter core from the middle of the onion, using an apple corer or paring knife, leaving the very bottom of the root end intact. Use a large sharp knife to slice about three-fourths of the way down center of the onion; turn onion 90 degrees and slice again. Keep slicing each section in half until you have 16 sections, being careful not to cut through the bottom of the onion. Spread sections apart.. Dip onion into milk mixture and then into flour mixture to coat, separating the petals and sprinkling flour mixture between them. Dip onion into milk mixture again, then into flour mixture to coat once more. Coat onion with cooking spray.. Arrange onion in the air fryer basket. Cook until crispy, 20 to 25 minutes.. Stir together mayonnaise, horseradish sauce, ketchup, paprika, salt, dried oregano, cayenne pepper, and black pepper in a small bowl. Chill until blooming onion is ready.. Serve blooming onion with dipping sauce and garnish with additional paprika.

name: Air Fryer Tempura Vegetables
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg whites'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'seltzer water'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'SEASONING (see Variations below)'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'VEGETABLES ('}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup purchased', 'name': 'DIPPING SAUCE'}
steps: Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Beat egg whites in a bowl until frothy. Whisk in seltzer wateruntil combined. Whisk in flour, SEASONING, salt, and pepper until batter forms.. Coat basket with cooking spray. Dip VEGETABLES into batter until coated; allow excess to drip off. Working in batches if needed, arrange vegetables in an even layer in basket. Cook until golden brown, about 7 minutes. Serve with DIPPING SAUCE.

name: Air Fryer Turtle Cheesecake
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'graham cracker crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'butter, melted'}, {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese, softened'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sour cream'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': '2'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'caramel ice cream topping, or to taste'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'pecans, or to taste'}
steps: Line the bottom of a 7- to 7 1/2-inch springform pan or cake pan with parchment paper. Stir together graham crackers and 1 tablespoon sugar in a bowl. Stir in melted butter. Press crumb mixture into the bottom and 1 inch up the sides of the prepared pan.. For the filling, combine cream cheese, sour cream, 1/3 cup sugar, lemon juice, vanilla, and salt in a bowl. Beat with an electric mixer at medium-high speed until smooth. Add eggs, 1 at a time, beating at low speed just until combined. Pour filling over the crust. Arrange pan in the air fryer basket.. Set air fryer to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C).. Cook for 15 minutes. Reduce temperature to 240 degrees F (115 degrees C) and cook 20 minutes more. The center of the cheesecake will appear wet and may jiggle slightly. Transfer cheesecake to a wire rack. Let stand about 15 minutes. Using a small sharp knife or thin spatula, loosen cheesecake from sides of pan; let stand until completely cooled, about 30 minutes more. Remove cheesecake from pan. Chill, covered, at least 4 hours or up to overnight.. To serve, drizzle with chocolate and caramel ice cream toppings and sprinkle with pecans.

name: Air Fryer Samosas
ingredients: {'quantity': '12', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'yukon gold potatoes,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'onion'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'fresh ginger'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garam masala'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cumin'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper (optional)'}, {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'frozen peas, thawed'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh cilantro, plus more for garnish'}, {'quantity': '24', 'unit': None, 'name': 'wonton wrappers'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole-milk Greek-style yogurt'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'fresh cilantro, plus more for garnish'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'lime zest'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lime juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, chopped'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'pinch', 'name': 'black pepper'}
steps: Add potatoes to a small saucepan and cover with salted water; bring to a boil over high heat. Reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes or until fork-tender. Drain and transfer potatoes to a bowl; mash until mostly smooth with a few small chunks remaining.. In the same saucepan, heat oil over medium heat. Add onion and cook, stirring occasionally, until tender, 3 to 4 minutes. Stir in ginger and garlic; cook until fragrant, about 30 seconds. Add garam masala, cumin, salt, and (if using) cayenne; cook about 30 seconds more. Stir in mashed potatoes and peas; cook until warmed through. Remove from heat; stir in cilantro.. Arrange wonton wrappers on a clean work surface; evenly spoon filling into centers of wontonwrappers. Lightly wet borders of wrappers withwater. Fold two corners together to form triangles. Press edges to seal. Coat both sides of samosas with cooking spray.. Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Coat air fryer basket with cooking spray.. Working in batches if needed, arrange samosas in an even layer in the basket. Cook, turning once halfway through, until samosas are golden brown and crispy, about 8 minutes.. Meanwhile, combine yogurt, cilantro, lime zest, lime juice; garlic, salt and pepper in a small food processor; process until well combined. Chill, covered, up to 5 days.. Serve samosas with cilantro-yogurt sauce. Garnish with additional cilantro.

name: Air Fryer Roasted Vegetables with Gremolata and Red Pepper Aioli
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'zucchini,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'medium', 'name': 'summer squash,'}, {'quantity': '1 (8-', 'unit': 'ounces package)', 'name': 'cremini mushrooms, halved or quartered if large'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'cauliflower florets'}, {'quantity': '6', 'unit': 'any color', 'name': 'mini bell peppers'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'vegetable oil'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup chopped', 'name': 'fresh parsley'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons minced', 'name': 'garlic'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'lemon zest'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': ''}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'extra-virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'red wine vinegar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic'}
steps: Preheat air fryer to 360 degrees F (180 degrees C).. Combine zucchini, summer squash, mushrooms, cauliflower, bell peppers, oil, salt, and black pepper in a bowl; toss to coat. Arrange vegetables in an even layer in the air fryer basket, working in batches if needed.. Cook, turning once halfway through, until tender, about 10 minutes.. Meanwhile, for gremolata, stir together parsley, garlic, and lemon zest in a small bowl.. For red pepper aioli stir together mayonnaise, roasted red peppers, olive oil, red wine vinegar; and garlic in a small bowl.. Top roasted vegetables with gremolata and serve with red pepper aioli.

name: Crab Rangoon in the Air Fryer
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'apricot fruit spread'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'chili-garlic sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon less-sodium', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'orange zest'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'freshly squeezed orange juice (from 1 orange)'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'crabmeat, drained'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'chives'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'orcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'clove', 'name': 'garlic, grated (about 1/2 teaspoon)'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '18', 'unit': None, 'name': 'wonton wrappers'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Stir together apricot spread, chili-garlic sauce, soy sauce, orange zest, and orange juice in a small bowl for the dipping sauce.. Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Stir together cream cheese, crab, chives, Worcestershire, garlic, pepper, and salt in a bowl for the filling. Arrange 6 wonton wrappers on a work surface. Keep remaining wrappers covered until ready to use to prevent them from drying out.. Spoon about 2 teaspoon crab filling in center of each wrapper. Lightly wet borders of wrapper with water. Bring together the 2 opposite corners of the wrapper over the filling and seal together. Bring remaining 2 corners up toward the center, sealing edges of the wrapper to enclose the filling. Repeat with remaining wrappers and filling.. Working in batches if needed, coat dumplings with cooking spray and arrange in an even layer in the air fryer basket.. Cook until dumplings are crispy and golden brown, about 8 minutes. Serve with sauce.

name: Air Fryer Everything-Bagel Salmon Dinner
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': None, 'name': 'sweet potato, cut into 1/4-inch wedges'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'olive oil, divided'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt, divided'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper, divided'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'broccoli florets'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'ounces)', 'name': 'salmon fillets'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'everything bagel seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'soy sauce'}
steps: Preheat air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C). Coat a sheet of foil with cooking spray.. Toss sweet potatoes with 1 1/2 teaspoons oil and 1/8 teaspoon each salt and pepper in a bowl. Arrange sweet potatoes in an even layer on the foil; transfer to the air fryer basket. Cook until mostly tender, about 10 minutes.. Meanwhile, stir together mustard, honey, and mayonnaise in a small bowl. In another bowl, toss broccoli with remaining 1 1/2 teaspoons oil and 1/8 teaspoon each salt and pepper.. Push sweet potatoes to one side of the basket. Add salmon to the other side. Spoon 1 teaspoon mustard mixture onto each fillet; spread to coat tops of fillets. Sprinkle evenly with bagel seasoning. Arrange broccoli around sweet potatoes and salmon. Cook until salmon is opaque and flakes easily with a fork and sweet potatoes and broccoli are tender, 10 to 14 minutes.. Stir soy sauce into the remaining mustard mixture; drizzle over sweet potatoes and broccoli to serve.

name: Air Fryer Crispy Pickle Chips with Creole Dipping Sauce
ingredients: {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1 (16-', 'unit': 'ounces jar) reduced-sodium', 'name': 'dill pickle chips, drained'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'mustard'}
steps: Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly coat air fryer basket with cooking spray.. Put flour in a shallow dish. In a second shallow dish, lightly beat eggs. In a third shallow dish, add panko. Pat pickle chips very dry. Coat pickles in flour, shaking off excess. Dip in eggs, allowing excess to drip off. Toss in panko, lightly pressing to adhere. Arrange pickles in the air fryer basket in an even layer (do not overcrowd), working in batches if needed.. Cook until pickle chips are golden brown, about 6 minutes.. Meanwhile, stir together mayonnaise, Creole mustard, lemon juice, and smoked paprika in a small bowl. Serve dipping sauce with pickles.

name: Air Fryer Raspberry Brownie Bites
ingredients: {'quantity': '2/3', 'unit': 'cup fresh or', 'name': 'frozen raspberries'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'cashew butter'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'dark chocolate, chopped'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsalted butter'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg yolk'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'sugar'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'vanilla extract'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'all purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'whole-wheat pastry flour'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'unsweetened cocoa powder'}
steps: Lightly coat 20 (13/4-inch) foil muffin cups with cooking spray.. Cook raspberries in a small saucepan over medium-low heat, stirring and crushing them with a fork, until broken down, 2 to 4 minutes. Transfer to a mini food processor. Add cashew butter and the water; purée until smooth.. Stir together dark chocolate, butter, and oil in a stainless-steel bowl. Set bowl over a saucepan of gently simmering water and melt ingredients, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat and stir until combined. Let cool about 20 minutes.. Combine egg, egg yolk, sugar, vanilla, and salt in another bowl. Beat with an electric mixer at medium-high until thickened, 3 to 5 minutes.. In a small bowl, whisk together flours and cocoa powder. Fold flour mixture, half at a time, into egg mixture until incorporated. With mixer running at medium-low, mix in melted chocolate mixture until well combined.. Spoon 2 teaspoons brownie batter into each prepared muffin cup. Layer 1 teaspoon raspberry mixture followed by 1/2 teaspoon brownie batter over top of each. Working in batches if needed, arrange muffin cups in an even layer in the air fryer basket.. Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Cook brownies in the preheated air fryer until set, about 5 minutes. Remove and cool on a wire rack. Brownies will keep chilled and covered for up to 3 days.

name: Air Fryer Sweet Potato Chips
ingredients: {'quantity': '1 large (8', 'unit': 'ounces)', 'name': 'sweet potato'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sea salt'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon freshly', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Slice potato into 1/16-inch-thick rounds using a mandoline. Put potato slices in a large bowl of cold water; soak about 20 minutes. Drain and pat dry with paper towels. Wipe out bowl.. Return potato slices to dried bowl. Add oil, salt, and pepper; toss gently to coat.. Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Lightly coat air fryer basket with cooking spray. Working in batches if needed, arrange potato slices in an even layer in basket (do not overcrowd).. Cook until lightly golden and crispy, 12 to 16 minutes, turning and rearranging chips into an even layer every 4 minutes. Watch closely during the last 2 to 3 minutes of cooking. Check chips about every 30 seconds, using tongs to remove golden chips from the basket as needed to avoid overcooking and ending up with bitter chips.. Let chips cool about 5 minutes. Chips will continue to crisp as they cool.Store in an airtight container up to 3 days.

name: Air Fryer Green Bean Fries
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'lb.', 'name': 'fresh green beans, trimmed'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'flour'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1/3', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'onion powder'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'lemon wedges for serving'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ketchup'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'dill pickle'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'steak seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}
steps: Combine beans and water in a saucepan, cover, and bring to a boil. Cook until beans are bright green and crisp-tender, about 4 minutes. Drain and transfer to a bowl of ice water.. Preheat air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C).. Put flour in a bowl. In another bowl, whisk together egg and milk. In a third bowl, stir together bread crumbs, chili powder, garlic powder, onion powder, and salt. Drain beans and pat dry with paper towels. Toss beans with flour to coat, shaking off excess. Dip into egg mixture and then into bread crumbs to coat, shaking off excess.. Working in batches if needed, arrange beans in an even layer in the air fryer basket and lightly coat with cooking spray. Cook, turning once halfway through, until golden brown, about 4 minutes. (If you like, keep fries warm in a 250 degrees F (95 degrees C) oven.). Meanwhile, stir together mayonnaise, ketchup, mustard, minced pickle, steak seasoning, and cayenne pepper in a small bowl for Special Sauce.. Serve green bean fries with Special Sauce and lemon wedges.

name: Air Fryer Loaded Egg Salad Sandwiches
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bacon, crisp-cooked and crumbled'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'stalks', 'name': 'celery, finely chopped'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'green onion'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'pickle relish'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'yellow mustard'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'Sriracha sauce'}, {'quantity': '3/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dried dill'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'orcestershire sauce'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/8', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'bread'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'leaves', 'name': 'romaine lettuce, torn'}
steps: Preheat air fryer to 250 degrees F (120 degrees C).. Arrange whole eggs in shells in an even layer in the fryer basket; cook for 20 minutes. Immediately plunge eggs into an ice bath. Let stand until cool, about 5 minutes; drain. Peel and coarsely chop eggs. Meanwhile, stir together bacon, celery, mayonnaise, onion, relish, mustard, sriracha, dill, Worcestershire, black pepper, paprika, and salt in a large bowl. Gently stir chopped eggs into mayonnaise mixture until combined. Chill, covered, at least 1 hour or up to 3 days. Serve egg salad in bread with lettuce.

name: Air Fryer Chicken Tenders
ingredients: {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'canola oil'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': None, 'name': 'chicken tenders (about 1 lb.)'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'fresh parsley, for garnish (optional)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'honey mustard sauce'}
steps: Preheat air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Coat basket with cooking spray.. Whisk egg in a small bowl. In another bowl, stir together panko and oil until loose and crumbly.. Dip each chicken tender into egg, allowing excess to drip off. Dip chicken in panko mixture to coat completely. Working in batches if needed, arrange chicken in an even layer in the air fryer basket.. Cook until chicken is no longer pink in the center and the juices run clear, about 12 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted into the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Garnish with parsley and serve with honey-mustard sauce.

name: Air Fryer Green Beans

steps: Preheat the air fryer to 380 degrees F (195 degrees C).. Place green beans, olive oil, lemon juice, salt, and pepper in a large bowl and toss to coat. name: Air Fryer Chicken Strips
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'boneless chicken breasts'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'pickle juice'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'liquid smoke'}, {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'eggs, at room temperature'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'ranch dressing'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all purpose flour, divided'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'white pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'garlic salt'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': "confectioners' sugar"}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'thyme'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'basil'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oregano'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'celery salt'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'dry mustard'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'ground ginger'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'chili powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'sea salt'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'coconut oil cooking spray'}
steps: Slice chicken breasts into 1-inch strips lengthwise and place in a shallow pan.. Whisk pickle juice, milk, and liquid smoke together in a cup; pour over chicken, and place chicken into the refrigerator to marinate for 30 minutes.. Meanwhile, whisk eggs and ranch dressing together in a shallow bowl. Place 1 cup flour in a separate shallow bowl.. Whisk remaining 1 cup flour, breadcrumbs, paprika, white pepper, garlic salt, confectioners’ sugar, thyme, basil, oregano, celery salt, black pepper, dry mustard, ginger, chili powder, and salt together in a third shallow bowl.. Preheat the air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Drain chicken strips and thoroughly dry with paper towels.. Dredge chicken strips in flour. then dip strips in egg mixture, letting the excess drip back into the bowl. Drop chicken strips, 1 at a time, in the breadcrumb mixture and coat thoroughly.. Lay strips in a single layer without touching into the air fryer basket. You may have to work in batches. Thoroughly spray with coconut oil.. Air fry for 6 minutes. Turn chicken over; spray with coconut oil, and continue to air fry until juices run clear and chicken is no longer pink at the center, about 6 more minutes. An instant read thermometer inserted near the center should read at least 165 degrees F (74 degrees C). Repeat with remaining chicken pieces.

name: Air Fryer Honey Garlic Chicken Wings
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'baking powder'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'salt'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'black pepper'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'garlic powder'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'paprika'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cayenne pepper'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'pounds', 'name': 'chicken wings'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'honey'}, {'quantity': '1/4', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'soy sauce'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, minced'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'ginger root'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'cornstarch'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'green onions'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Mix baking powder, salt, black pepper, garlic powder, paprika, and cayenne pepper together in a small bowl.. Pat chicken wings dry with paper towels, then toss them in spice mixture until evenly coated. Arrange wings in a single layer in the air fryer basket.. Cook wings in the preheated air fryer until crispy and golden brown, juices are clear, and meat is no longer pink at the bone, 20 to 25 minutes. An instant-read thermometer inserted near the bone should read 165 degrees F (74 degrees C).. Meanwhile, make the honey garlic sauce. Stir honey, soy sauce, garlic, and ginger together in a small saucepan over medium heat.. In a separate small bowl, whisk together cornstarch and water until smooth, then add to the saucepan. Cook until sauce thickens, 1 to 2 minutes.. Transfer wings to a large bowl, pour honey garlic sauce over wings, and toss to coat evenly. Garnish with chopped green onions and serve hot.

name: Air Fryer Pizookie
ingredients: {'quantity': '5', 'unit': 'pieces', 'name': 'pre-cut refrigerated chocolate chip cookie dough'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'scoop', 'name': 'vanilla gelato (optional)'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'whipped cream,'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'ounce', 'name': 'chocolate'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 360 degrees F (175 degrees C).. Get a large piece of aluminum foil and fold it into an 8x8-inch square. You can make a little dish out of the foil by folding the edges upward.. Place 1 piece of cookie dough in the middle of your foil. Arrange remaining cookie dough pieces around it in a pattern similar to the 5-side of a die.. Bake cookie in the air fryer for 6 minutes. Open the air fryer and gently push down the top of the cookie; continue to bake until deep golden brown, 2 to 4 minutes more.. Add gelato, whipped cream, and a drizzle of melted chocolate, and enjoy!

name: Air Fryer Cheese Curds
ingredients: {'quantity': '3', 'unit': 'cloves', 'name': 'garlic, peeled'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'extra virgin olive oil'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'soul food seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1/2', 'unit': 'cup', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'lemon juice'}, {'quantity': '10', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'cheese curds'}, {'quantity': '1 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'all-purpose flour'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'soul food seasoning'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1 1/2', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'milk'}, {'quantity': '2 1/4', 'unit': 'cups', 'name': 'panko bread crumbs'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'oil, or as needed for spraying'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: For Aioli: Combine garlic cloves, olive oil, and the 1/2 teaspoon soul seasoning in a small bowl and toss to coat. Wrap garlic tightly in a small piece of foil.. Preheat the air fryer to 375 degrees F (190 degrees C). Place wrapped garlic in the air fryer basket, and air fry for 15 minutes.. Remove garlic from the air fryer and place in a small bowl. Mash roasted garlic with the back of a spoon. Let stand for 30 minutes.. Stir mayonnaise and lemon juice into the mashed garlic until well combined. Cover and refrigerate for 30 minutes before serving.. For Cheese Curds: Place cheese curds on a large rimmed baking sheet lined with parchment paper. Place the tray with cheese curds in the freezer for 30 minutes.. Meanwhile, whisk flour and 1 teaspoon soul seasoning together in a shallow bowl. Whisk eggs and milk together In a separate bowl until smooth and cohesive. Stir panko and remaining 3 teaspoons soul seasoning together in a third shallow bowl.. Remove cheese curds from the freezer. Working in batches, dip cheese curds into the flour to coat well, then into the egg mixture, making sure to shake off any excess. Dip curds again in flour mixture and again into egg mixture. Finally, dip curds into panko to fully coat with breadcrumbs. Use your dry hand to pack on panko so that it sticks well. Place breaded cheese curds back onto the baking sheet. When all cheese curds are breaded, return the baking sheet to the freezer for 30 minutes.. Preheat the air fryer to 350 degrees F (175 degrees C). Remove tray from freezer. Using a mister, lightly spray both sides of the cheese curds with vegetable oil. Coat the air fryer basket with nonstick cooking spray.. Working in batches, place cheese curds in the air fryer basket in a single layer. Air fry until golden brown and crispy on both sides, flipping halfway through cooking time, 4 to 6 minutes.. Let stand in the air fryer for 1 to 2 minutes before serving. Serve with roasted garlic aioli.

name: Air Fryer Grilled Ham and Cheese
ingredients: {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'mayonnaise'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'white bread'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'tablespoons', 'name': 'ijon mustard'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'slices', 'name': 'deli ham'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'large slices', 'name': 'wiss cheese'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': None, 'name': 'dill pickle slices'}, {'quantity': None, 'unit': None, 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Spread mayonnaise on one side of each slice of bread. Flip, and cook until cheese has melted and sandwiches are golden brown, 2 to 3 minutes more. Slice sandwiches in half and serve warm.

name: Air Fryer Bacon Wrapped Brussels Sprouts

name: Quick Air Fryer Tilapia

name: Air Fryer Chickpeas

name: Air Fryer Chicken Bites with Parmesan Cheese

steps: Whisk olive oil, Worcestershire, Italian seasoning, garlic powder, salt, and pepper together in a bowl. Add chicken cubes and stir to coat.. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese and parsley over the chicken. Cook until cheese has started to melt, about 2 minutes more. Serve immediately.

name: Air Fryer Mini Croissants with Nutella and Jam
ingredients: {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'sheet', 'name': 'frozen puff pastry, thawed'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'large', 'name': 'egg'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'tablespoon', 'name': 'water'}, {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'chocolate-hazelnut spread (such as Nutella®)'}, {'quantity': '4', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'strawberry jam'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': 'teaspoon', 'name': 'cinnamon sugar, or as needed'}
steps: Preheat air fryer to 300 degrees F (150 degrees C).. Roll out puff pastry on a lightly floured surface into a large square, about 12 inches. Cut into 4 equal squares, and then cut each square in half diagonally, making 8 triangles.. Position the triangle so the wide end is facing you, and the point is away from you. Dip your finger tip in some water, and moisten the edges of each triangle. Whisk the egg and tablespoon of water in a small bowl, and set aside.. Add about 1 teaspoon Nutella to the center, and top with about 1/2 teaspoon strawberry jam. Starting on the wide end, roll up dough over the filling toward the point, pinching in the dough, so the filling doesn't ooze out, and shaping the ends into a crescent shape. Brush each crescent with egg wash and sprinkle with cinnamon sugar.. Line your air fryer basket with a parchment liner or spray with cooking spray. Place the croissants into your air fryer basket, seam side down, so they're not touching.. Cook in the air fryer until golden brown,11 to 14 minutes. Your cooking time may vary depending on the size and brand of your air fryer.. Transfer to a wire rack and cool for 5 minutes. Serve warm.

name: Air Fryer Cherry Cream Cheese Croissants
ingredients: {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'flour for dusting'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) package', 'name': 'refrigerated crescent roll dough (such as Pillsbury®'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(8 ounce) tub', 'name': 'cream cheese'}, {'quantity': '1', 'unit': '(15 ounce) can', 'name': 'pitted sour cherries, drained'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'ground cinnamon to taste'}
steps: Lightly dust a work surface with flour. Unroll crescent dough and divide into triangles along the perforated lines.. Spread each triangle with cream cheese.. Drop 3 or 4 cherries on the wider portion of each crescent dough triangle. Carefully roll up each crescent, making sure the cherries stay tucked in. Fold down the ends of each roll slightly so it forms a crescent shape.. Spray the basket of the air fryer with non stick cooking spray spray. Carefully set the croissants into the basket.. Set air fryer to 400 degrees F (200 degrees C).. Air fry croissants until puffed up and lightly browned, about 5 minutes. Check to make sure croissants are not sticking to each other and that they are not overly browned. Continue cooking for 2 to 3 minutes longer, making sure they do not get too done.. Transfer croissants to a plate and sprinkle with cinnamon.

name: Air Fryer Halloumi
ingredients: {'quantity': '8', 'unit': 'ounces', 'name': 'halloumi cheese'}, {'quantity': '2', 'unit': 'teaspoons', 'name': 'olive oil'}, {'quantity': '', 'unit': '', 'name': 'cooking spray'}
steps: Preheat the air fryer to 360 degrees F (180 degrees C).. Slice halloumi into 6 equal slices, cut each slice in half, and dry with a paper towel. Brush all sides with olive oil.. Lightly spray the air fryer basket with cooking spray. Place the halloumi slices in the basket, making sure they're not touching. You may have to cook in two batches,. Cook for 7 to 9 minutes until golden brown, but make sure not to overcook or they turn rubbery. Serve immediately.
